        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 1 at 4:38PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 437 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of De Beque, or 20 miles east of Grand Junction, moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail followed by
moderate snow rates which could impact area roadways.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mesa, Plateau City, Cameo, Molina, and Collbran.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 45 and 58.
Colorado 65 between mile markers 46 and 61.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
